{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566604"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:44:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:44:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18854"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18854","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18854"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.84,0.03,0.09,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11587"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79740"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11587","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11587"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18854"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65044"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11305"},{"type":"tags","id":"11308"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27264"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27266"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79740","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79740"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ESexual harassment in healthcare settings can manifest in various ways. Understanding what constitutes inappropriate workplace behaviour is essential for maintaining a safe and respectful environment.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes behaviour that constitutes sexual harassment in a healthcare workplace?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Commenting on a colleague\u0027s weight loss after their return from leave","Unwanted repeated comments about physical appearance","Sharing personal relationship experiences during breaks","Making jokes about dating preferences in group settings","Suggesting social activities outside work hours"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Eunwanted repeated comments about physical appearance\u003C/strong\u003E. This represents sexual harassment as it involves unwelcome behaviour of a sexual nature that can make the recipient feel offended, humiliated or intimidated. The repetitive nature and focus on physical attributes rather than professional qualities makes this inappropriate workplace behaviour.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommenting on a colleague\u0027s weight loss after their return from leave\u003C/strong\u003E - While potentially inappropriate, a single comment about appearance may not constitute sexual harassment unless it has sexual undertones or is part of a pattern\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESharing personal relationship experiences during breaks\u003C/strong\u003E - While potentially unprofessional, this may not constitute sexual harassment unless explicit or unwanted\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaking jokes about dating preferences in group settings\u003C/strong\u003E - While inappropriate for the workplace, this may not specifically target an individual\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuggesting social activities outside work hours\u003C/strong\u003E - This may be inappropriate depending on context but is not inherently sexual harassment unless accompanied by unwanted romantic or sexual overtones\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESexual harassment in healthcare settings can include unwanted sexual advances, inappropriate comments, sharing of sexual material, or creating an intimidating environment. It is important to recognise that power imbalances in healthcare hierarchies can make it difficult for recipients to speak up or refuse unwanted attention.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Sexual harassment includes any unwelcome sexual behaviour that makes a person feel offended, humiliated or intimidated.","Healthcare professionals have a legal and ethical obligation to report sexual harassment in the workplace.","Sexual harassment can take many forms including verbal, physical, or written/electronic communications."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Cedeno R, Bohlen J. Sexual Harassment and Prevention Training. 2024 Mar 29. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan\u2013. PMID: 36508513. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36508513/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65044"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18854"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65044","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65044"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-15T13:57:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-15T13:57:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11587"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79740"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"http